President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday hosted Senate Deputy Minority Leader Senator Emmanuel Bwacha at the Presidential Villa in Abuja, following his defection to the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). Bwacha, who is representing Taraba South, defected from the main opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP).   Fed Govt committed to police reforms, human rights…     N2.9b fraud allegation: Okorocha seeks Buhari’s…     Glo Battle of the Year Nigeria to begin Saturday   His defection was announced yesterday when the Chairman of APC National Caretaker Committee and Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni presented him to President Buhari at the State House in Abuja. The President, accompanied by his Chief of Staff, Prof. Ibrahim Gambari, welcomed the senator and latest entrant into the ruling party. Addressing reporters after the meeting with the President, Bwacha said he joined  the APC because he was sure he would get a level-playing field in the party.